1.Explain how and why java came into existence.
Ans1. Java was basically developed by James Gosling at Sun Microsystems. Java is platform independent and we can run java on any platform  ,  also they want to make such
language which is small , robust , platform independent because languages like c is not platform independent 

2.State the difference between JVM,JDK & JRE.
Ans2.  Lets start with the abbrevations
		JVM - Java Virtual Machine  ,  JDK - Java Development Kit   ,  JRE - Java Runtime Environment
The jre is set of softwre tools designed for runnning software other . Every user need this to run the java program.
The jvm provide its users with a platform independent way for executing the java codes , It consiste of libraries and frameworks.
Th jdk consists of various tools rquired for writing the java programs. Provides environment to execute the java source code.

3.Explain why is java portable.
Ans3.java is portable because it can compile a java code which will give us the byte code and then we can run that code with java virtual machine  

